{
  "stem": "1918.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Eventually he, he became a-- he created a bookstore on the Lower East Side, which he brought in all of the books that could be salvaged from the European tragedy.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was a successful businessman in selling.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He went to Europe and brought back whatever he could save.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And his first love was the Talmud, and now he was back in the business of Talmudic books.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he stayed here all the years.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we had one or two communications from him, and then nothing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And whatever he learned about the war here no doubt made him the most devastated man in the world.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And nothing he could do except keep-- as a matter of fact, he finally got the papers to come to America.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For the six children and my mother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he finally got the papers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But instead of giving it to him with all deliberate haste-- since he was already here and probably in the process of applying for American citizenship, and most of us were underaged, and we were legitimate-- but they just teased him, or whatever the hell they did, but they didn't give him the papers.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And finally, when they did give it to him to go to America, it was-- [SIGHS] We went to Budapest, my mother and one of my sisters, Chica and I, to see the American Consul to get visas on Monday morning.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this was Sunday afternoon.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we heard that-- it was Sunday morning that Japan-- it was Pearl Harbor.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the Americans entered the war, so the--",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--the papers were useless.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And because we were-- Hungary was an ally of Hitler, and, and America entered the War on the side of the Allies.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
